50|$|Searchlights {{were used}} {{extensively}} in defense against nighttime bomber raids during the Second World War. Controlled by <b>sound</b> <b>locators</b> and radars, searchlights could track bombers, indicating targets to anti-aircraft guns and night fighters and dazzling crews.|$|R
5000|$|Early war tactics for the {{searchlight}} deployment had the searchlights {{forward of}} the Flak guns in a [...] "zone of preparation", {{laid out in a}} grid with 5 kilometers between each light. <b>Sound</b> <b>locators</b> deployed with the searchlights helped them find targets, later these were replaced with radar systems.|$|R
