2500|$|In mid-March the {{regiment}} began a partial deployment without searchlights to guard Vulnerable Points (VPs) {{in the light}} anti-aircraft [...] (LAA) role, equipped with 20mm guns (Oerlikon or Hispano) and Lewis guns. The regiment received its first 150cm searchlights in April, by which time RHQ had returned to Kilmarnock. It became operational, equipped with 90cm and 150cm S/L projectors, <b>sound</b> <b>locators</b> and electrical generators, on 9 May during a Luftwaffe raid. The following night, Rudolf Hess landed by parachute some 200 yards from one of {{the regiment}}'s sites and was apprehended by the local Home Guard unit.|$|R
